_source.text: [ 121 ] When he met Chamberlain for the first time, Wilhelm told him: "I thank you for what you have done for Germany!". [ 121 ] The next day, Eulenburg wrote to a friend that the Emperor "stood completely under the spell of this man [Chamberlain], whom he understood better than any of the other guests because of his thorough study of The Foundations ".
